ink.";i:21;s:51:"This also disables any remotes or wireless keypads.";i:22;s:33:"Thanks to everyone on this forum.";i:23;s:127:"Had a 15 year old Craftsman 12 HP garage door opener that would open with remote and panel but would not close with the remote.";i:24;s:80:"I noticed that the bulb on the garage opener turned on when it opened or closed.";i:25;s:77:"The garage door would only go down using the remote once the bulb turned off.";i:26;s:97:"When your garage door wont open with the remote there are few things that can cause this problem.";i:27;s:26:"You might be out of range.";i:28;s:69:"The antenna on the motor could be damaged or blocked from the signal.";i:29;s:44:"Make sure it is hanging down from the motor.";i:30;s:47:"If all these fail try reprogramming the remote.";i:31;s:115:"If your garage door remote does not seem to work whenever you press it then it may be experiencing RF interference.";i:32;s:115:"When this happens your garage door will not receive your remotes signal and its likely there is an RF interference.";i:33;s:86:"Often motion detectors home alarm systems and electronic game systems are behind this.";i:34;s:79:"I know that it is very frustrating to have issues with your garage door opener.";i:35;s:104:"First be sure the issue is not with the range of the remotes being reduced by some form of interference.";i:36;s:70:"Look for the LED on the opener to flash when you push a remote button.";i:37;s:92:"If there is no flash then the opener might not be receiving a signal from the remote at all.";i:38;s:141:"The garage door opens with the wall switch and even sometimes with the remote but it doesnt close with the remotes only with the wall switch.";i:39;s:35:"Sandra armenta on December 07 2018.";i:40;s:58:"Carwall and control on the wall garage door will not open.";i:41;s:59:"I do not hear the motor running but the light does turn on.";i:42;s:27:"Carol on September 30 2018.";i:43;s:58:"If the door operates the problem is in the wire or button.";